{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As you pass the time on your phone, do you dutifully notice noises in the next room and listen for indications that everything is okay, or are you completely oblivious?",
    "Likewise, if you see that your best friend is depressed, but you know she'd rather not talk about it, you might pretend not to notice.",
    "If so, then you act no differently than if you actually failed to notice her poor state.",
    "But part of what it is to be a good friend is to notice such things.",
    "And the special attention friends owe to each other in virtue of their friendship doesn't just promote further goods for them-though of course it can and often does do that-it also instantiates the value they place on their relationship and constitutes their love for each other (Kolodny, 2003)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "And the special attention friends owe to each other in virtue of their friendship doesn't just promote further goods for them-though of course it can and often does do that-it also instantiates the value they place on their relationship and constitutes their love for each other (Kolodny, 2003)."
